<br>
My response...<br>
<br>
It's really a matter of what you consider adventure or &quot;epic encounter&quot; as you put it.  For you triggering a huge elemental and whatching him come over the horizon is and &quot;epic adventure&quot; for you.  And that is good. I am glad people look at this game as more of an adventure.  But I don't see where you warrant your plea that this epic is &quot;hard&quot;.  I was mainly discussion how hard the mage epic is.  As for the &quot;epic encounter part&quot;, for me (and just as your opinion on epic encounter is correct as it is a matter of opinion, so is mine) planning a Hate raid a week in advance, calling and porting to the troops to the base point, then porting them up in break in teams, and watching us bust lots of mobs at the portal only to eventually see the elusive Magi spawn and grin from ear to ear if he is carrying the staff.  Then to get to watch the hunched-back pale skinned vampire flip back on his butt when he dies.....   I consider that &quot;an epic encounter&quot; for me.<br>
<br>
Just out of curiosity..... when you killed Ixi how many mages with their fire pets helped?   Then I would also ask how many mages have you helped make an attempt at the hate staff or crown?  And I mean went to hate where the only intention was to get the mage epic.  Not talking about all the hate raids you have been on where a mage was present.  Just curious, from a statistical probability stand point, I am not accusing you of anything.<br>
<br>
<br>
As for your bash on Verants versions of the story lines behind the epics....<br>
<br>
<br>
It's all a matter of what you prefer.  Some people like the writings of The lord of the rings.  Some people like Stephen King.  Some people like romance novels.  I feel that it is inappropriate for you to say that because you don't like the story line behind a certain epic ( or if it does not make any sense to you ) , then it is really shouldn't be considered epic.  Some epics require that you purchase things.  Many would feel that is not considered epic.  Other people do.  <br>
<br>
My original intentions were simply to help lighten the frustration that clerics are now having.  My referencing the mage  epic was in hopes to get clerics to say &quot;yeah, I guess it could be worse&quot;<br>
